                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Court bar on Sobhraj fiancee
          J. HEMANTH                           Nihita Biswas                                  
	Kathmandu, Aug. 4: Nepals Supreme Court today ordered the detention of Charles Sobhrajs fiancee Nihita Biswas and her mother Shakuntala Thapa till contempt petition hearing against them was completed.         
	An apex court division bench comprising of Justices Balaram KC and Ram Kumar Prasad gave the order after the hearing could not be completed today. It will resume tomorrow. As a result of the order, Biswas and Thapa were taken into custody.         
	Earlier, Biswas and her mother, who is also one of Sobhrajs lawyers, appeared in court in response to the summons issued to them yesterday. The petition was filed by two lawyers after Biswas and Thapa accused the judges of corruption.                                                                                                                                                           
